# Git Workflow (YAMTAM)

## Commit Format
```
<type>: <description>

Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore, perf, ci
```

## Before git push — run ALL gates
```bash
bash core/tests/skills/test-skill-triggering.sh   # must show Result: PASS
bash core/scripts/verify-skills-lock.sh            # no drift
bash core/scripts/drift-check.sh                   # CLEAN
git status --short                                 # no unintended changes
```

One FAIL = push blocked. No exceptions.

## Hard rules
- `git push --force` — NEVER
- `git reset --hard` — never without explicit user instruction
- `git push origin main` — only after all gates pass
- Commit messages: no "WIP", no "fix", no "update" alone — be specific

## Feature workflow
1. Plan first (`/plan`) if touching 3+ files
2. TDD: write failing test → implement → verify
3. Code review before merge
4. Detailed commit message (why, not what)
